Changed her name
back to baylor,

40:19.451 --> 40:21.084
got Walker's name
changed to baylor,

40:21.086 --> 40:25.054
and then just cut the sanford
right out her life.

40:25.056 --> 40:27.056
It's not like
i had a choice.

40:27.058 --> 40:30.727
Mama and daddy told me
point blank

40:30.729 --> 40:31.694
I couldn't come home,

40:31.696 --> 40:33.029
that I had a husband
and that was that.

40:33.031 --> 40:35.632
Well, they took up for Wes,
it's true.

40:35.634 --> 40:38.168
They just didn't know
any better.

40:38.170 --> 40:38.768
Really?

40:38.770 --> 40:41.104
Didn't know better
than to refuse

40:41.106 --> 40:43.173
to give their daughter
and grandbaby a damn penny?

40:43.175 --> 40:44.974
You know Wes never paid
any child support.

40:44.976 --> 40:48.178
Only time he'd call
was when he was all lit up,

40:48.180 --> 40:51.581
crying about missing his boy
and then crying

40:51.583 --> 40:52.615
'cause that boy was dead.

40:52.617 --> 40:55.685
Well, he felt bad about it.
- Says you.

40:55.687 --> 40:57.487
No, Wes is not always
a monster.

40:57.489 --> 41:01.191
Is. - So Wes is always a monster,
your parents were monsters.

41:01.193 --> 41:03.960
Everybody who ever did you
any wrong is a monster.

41:03.962 --> 41:06.963
That's right.
- Oh, poor, poor pitiful Darcy.

41:06.965 --> 41:08.898
Shut up, ml.

41:18.576 --> 41:20.910
Hey.

41:23.013 --> 41:24.547
You okay?

41:24.549 --> 41:25.949
Yeah.

42:11.028 --> 42:12.795
Darcy?

42:14.131 --> 42:15.865
Darce?

42:30.281 --> 42:32.048
Oh, my god.

42:35.019 --> 42:36.819
Wes.

42:40.791 --> 42:43.026
Wes.

42:43.028 --> 42:45.328
It's me, Darcy.

42:48.799 --> 42:51.935
Okay with you
if I sit down?

43:05.849 --> 43:07.617
Wes.

43:09.920 --> 43:11.220
I don't know if you can
understand

43:11.222 --> 43:13.690
a word I'm about to say,

43:13.692 --> 43:17.594
but I came here
to talk to you about our boy.

43:34.078 --> 43:36.646
You recognize this?

43:38.382 --> 43:41.684
You said it was part
of his legacy.

43:41.686 --> 43:44.988
It's part of his legacy,
all right.

43:44.990 --> 43:46.923
Remember?

43:48.726 --> 43:53.630
You gave it to him
on the day he was born.

43:56.400 --> 43:59.402
That was your...

43:59.404 --> 44:01.938
Idea of a...

44:01.940 --> 44:04.874
Baby present,
i guess.

44:08.979 --> 44:10.146
I was thinking about it

44:10.148 --> 44:13.683
Standing out
on Mary Lou's balcony

44:13.685 --> 44:14.784
last night.

44:14.786 --> 44:18.021
I can't even explain to you
what it was like

44:18.023 --> 44:21.024
watching that baby shoot
right out from between my legs

44:21.026 --> 44:25.962
when he'd been inside me
for so long.

44:25.964 --> 44:28.431
And then he was there.

44:28.866 --> 44:33.069
And when they put him in
my arms wrapped up so tight,

44:33.071 --> 44:36.673
and...
and I thought, oh...

44:36.675 --> 44:38.174
Look at you.

44:39.877 --> 44:42.445
You're a dreamer.

44:43.881 --> 44:46.916
You're my baby boy.

44:49.086 --> 44:54.123
I hope the world doesn't knock
that sweetness out of you.

44:58.796 --> 45:00.697
When I walked into
the house that night

45:00.699 --> 45:03.266
and saw his sneakers
sitting by the back door,

45:03.268 --> 45:05.368
I called out his name.

45:05.370 --> 45:06.736
I figured...

45:06.738 --> 45:10.473
It was too hot
in that apartment of his,

45:10.475 --> 45:13.876
and he'd come home
to cool off.

45:15.813 --> 45:19.382
He'd been so anxious.

45:19.384 --> 45:21.451
So goddamn anxious
all the time.

45:21.453 --> 45:24.353
I walked back
to check on him

45:24.355 --> 45:27.457
and walked into his room.

45:28.726 --> 45:32.028
Oh, oh, oh...

45:54.419 --> 45:56.853
You hear those birds?

45:57.788 --> 45:59.489
Do you?

46:01.291 --> 46:03.092
Do you?

46:04.828 --> 46:07.029
Do you?
Do you hear them?

46:38.428 --> 46:40.530
Good-bye, Wes.

47:11.895 --> 47:13.229
hey.
- Hey, you're back.

47:13.231 --> 47:18.067
I just, uh, stepped out
for a little cup of coffee.

47:18.069 --> 47:20.102
This came for you.

47:20.104 --> 47:22.238
It's from geri.

47:31.983 --> 47:36.052
But... so Mr. Wright's
not available

47:36.054 --> 47:37.386
until tomorrow morning.

47:37.388 --> 47:40.189
You're sure there's nothing
later today?

47:40.191 --> 47:42.558
Darce, I gotta get back.
I can't stay away that long.

47:42.560 --> 47:46.596
Shh, shh!
Uh-huh, yeah, of course.

47:46.598 --> 47:48.898
He's only got
one spot free tomorrow.

47:48.900 --> 47:50.299
I can't do that.

47:50.301 --> 47:53.269
Mm-hmm, yeah,
well, I'm in meridian,

47:53.271 --> 47:55.404
but I have contacts
in Jackson and hattiesburg,

47:55.406 --> 48:00.643
and we would just love to get
a Mississippi franchise going.

48:00.645 --> 48:03.946
Great. 11:30?

48:05.048 --> 48:08.017
Yes,
my name is Addie bundren.

48:08.019 --> 48:10.386
Yes, I will see you then.

48:10.388 --> 48:13.022
Where in the hell did you get
that crazy name from?

48:13.024 --> 48:16.993
Faulkner.
- Relax that smart thing, baby.

48:21.531 --> 48:24.934
why are you always asking me
to be specific?

48:24.936 --> 48:26.669
You know
that's not how I operate.

48:26.671 --> 48:29.438
Oh, I think you're
very specific, Darcy.

48:29.440 --> 48:31.474
You just don't like
to admit that you are.

48:31.476 --> 48:34.176
It goes against the image
you like to promote.

48:34.178 --> 48:36.946
And what's that?

48:36.948 --> 48:38.648
Free spirit.

48:40.350 --> 48:44.353
I do consider myself
something of a free spirit.

48:44.355 --> 48:47.523
Nothing about
your spirit is free.

49:14.118 --> 49:17.153
you just have to trust me
that it was pressing.

49:17.155 --> 49:18.354
You know I'm not the type...

49:18.356 --> 49:22.992
<i>please insert 25 cents
for another three minutes.</i>

49:24.428 --> 49:28.331
You know I'm not the type
of person to just...

49:28.333 --> 49:31.000
no,
of course I understand.

49:31.368 --> 49:35.705
Well, I'll think real hard
about what you said.

49:37.441 --> 49:39.141
All right.

49:39.143 --> 49:41.978
See you back in the office.

49:49.519 --> 49:51.187
Want me to wrap that up?
- Oh, yeah.

49:51.189 --> 49:54.991
I'd like to finish my food
if you don't mind.

49:56.259 --> 49:59.328
That he was going to have
to bring in another assistant

49:59.330 --> 50:01.564
to fix it,
and that I know full well

50:01.566 --> 50:02.698
what the situation is

50:02.700 --> 50:05.134
and do I want to hang onto
my job or not?

50:05.136 --> 50:07.069
Well, do you?
- Of course I do.

50:07.071 --> 50:09.705
What about your application?
- What about it?

50:09.707 --> 50:10.506
I talked to geri.

50:10.508 --> 50:13.242
She says if you finish it up
by Friday, she can sneak it in.

50:13.244 --> 50:16.412
You just gotta finish it.

50:23.653 --> 50:25.755
I thought you wanted to make
something more of yourself.

50:25.757 --> 50:27.390
That's what
you've been saying to me

50:27.392 --> 50:29.025
for god knows
how many years now.

50:29.027 --> 50:31.127
So don't you sit there
and just throw up your hands

50:31.129 --> 50:32.628
and let this opportunity
pass you by.

50:32.630 --> 50:35.264
You can still fix it.
Just turn around.

50:35.266 --> 50:38.200
And not go find
buford lapierre?

50:38.202 --> 50:39.602
We're only about 25 miles away.

50:39.604 --> 50:42.671
Are you suggesting I skip
going to New Orleans altogether?

50:42.673 --> 50:45.541
What the hell did we come
all this way for then?

50:55.819 --> 50:59.355
<i> A couple days ago,
the army corps of engineers</i>

50:59.357 --> 51:00.523
<i>opened up the spillway</i>

51:00.525 --> 51:03.626
<i>to take some of the pressure
off the Mississippi.</i>

51:03.628 --> 51:05.795
<i>They divert the excess water</i>

51:05.797 --> 51:07.329
<i>right into
the atchafalaya river.</i>

51:07.331 --> 51:10.533
<i> Yeah, and that means
that the low-lying towns,</i>

51:10.535 --> 51:11.634
<i>they just flood out.</i>

51:11.636 --> 51:13.536
<i> Well, our neighbors
in the north, Mississippi,</i>

51:13.538 --> 51:16.672
<i>Georgia, Alabama,
and the carolinas and beyond</i>

51:16.674 --> 51:18.507
<i>aren't getting a drop
of rain,</i>

51:18.509 --> 51:21.844
<i>but down here in Louisiana,
the low-lying parishes</i>

51:21.846 --> 51:24.580
<i>the water's rising real fast,
folks.</i>

51:24.582 --> 51:27.083
<i>So I need ask you,
what would you take from home</i>

51:27.085 --> 51:31.253
<i>if somebody gave you
just 30 minutes to evacuate?</i>

51:32.556 --> 51:34.190
Hey!

51:34.192 --> 51:36.625
How do I go about
getting on that road?

51:36.627 --> 51:39.261
Where are y'all headed?
- Simone city.

51:39.263 --> 51:41.363
No, you can't
go down there, ma'am.

51:41.365 --> 51:43.232
The whole damn parish
is flooded out.

51:43.234 --> 51:44.667
But I got somebody
i gotta meet.

51:44.669 --> 51:47.870
Well, you got to turn around
and go back the way you come.

51:47.872 --> 51:50.272
Take a left down
at the end of this road.

51:50.274 --> 51:50.706
Uh-huh.

51:50.708 --> 51:52.608
Then follow it all
the way down till it ends again.

51:52.610 --> 51:55.845
Then ask somebody where
the Saint Luke church is.

51:55.847 --> 51:57.813
All right.
- All right then, yeah?

51:57.815 --> 52:00.616
Thanks a lot.
- Y'all be careful.

52:52.936 --> 52:55.404
Buford lapierre?

53:02.579 --> 53:05.481
Any of y'all know
a buford lapierre?

53:05.749 --> 53:08.751
Do y'all know when you
can get some shelter?

53:08.753 --> 53:09.785
Church is full up.

53:09.787 --> 53:11.954
They said they're gonna
bus us somewhere.

53:11.956 --> 53:15.624
Buford lapierre!
- Who wants him?

53:17.861 --> 53:20.396
They told me my <i> grandpere</i>
was coming on the next bus.

53:20.398 --> 53:23.532
But we ain't seen him.
My baby's hungry.

53:23.534 --> 53:25.401
My wife's trying to get
her asthma meds.

53:25.403 --> 53:26.735
What I'm trying to say
is that right now,

53:26.737 --> 53:29.371
I can't be bothering about
something out of the past.

53:29.373 --> 53:31.407
Ain't no concern
of mine.

53:31.409 --> 53:34.343
I-i know, it's just...

53:34.345 --> 53:37.513
I drove all this way
to speak with you.

53:37.515 --> 53:39.215
So I'm just...

53:39.217 --> 53:41.550
I'm asking you kindly
if you'll recollect

53:41.552 --> 53:46.255
anything about my boy...
- I recollect what matters to me.

53:46.257 --> 53:48.991
No! Please wait.

53:51.761 --> 53:54.730
Try to remember
how he happened

53:54.732 --> 53:59.301
to walk out of that room with
a box of bullets in his hand.

54:01.671 --> 54:06.508
We were partying that night.
What can I say about that?

54:06.510 --> 54:08.010
I'm straight edge now, though.

54:08.012 --> 54:09.945
I got nothing to do
with that stuff.

54:09.947 --> 54:13.315
I don't even like
to think about it.

54:13.317 --> 54:16.685
I will say I never liked
that guy mark.

54:16.687 --> 54:18.354
Real superior.

54:18.356 --> 54:21.257
I didn't like it that his daddy
bought him that house

54:21.259 --> 54:22.591
and I had to pay rent on it
neither.

54:22.593 --> 54:26.362
It was like that guy mark
saw the weakness in your boy,

54:26.364 --> 54:28.430
saw he was hurting
in some sense.

54:28.432 --> 54:31.000
He had so much money,
never could figure out

54:31.002 --> 54:32.434
why he wouldn't
just lend him some.

54:32.436 --> 54:35.804
Wait, Walker was trying
to borrow money?

54:35.806 --> 54:37.006
Yeah, so he could graduate.

54:37.008 --> 54:39.942
He didn't think
he was gonna make it.

54:39.944 --> 54:42.411
He was like a cat
playing with a mouse,

54:42.413 --> 54:46.415
poking at the bleeding spots,
saying stuff like,

54:46.417 --> 54:48.617
"seems like you in a lot
of pain, you in pain",

54:48.619 --> 54:51.754
and, "sometimes a tunnel
is just a tunnel",

54:51.756 --> 54:52.855
that kind of shit.

54:52.857 --> 54:54.957
I thought it was just
the drugs talking,

54:54.959 --> 54:57.026
but later I figured
that that guy saw

54:57.028 --> 55:01.397
some kind of door opening up,
just got Walker out of the way,

55:01.399 --> 55:02.931
he could step right through it.

55:02.933 --> 55:06.735
So when he drove Walker back
to town later that night...

55:06.737 --> 55:08.504
wait.

55:08.506 --> 55:11.407
Mark Wright drove Walker
to my house?

55:11.409 --> 55:13.509
None of the rest of us
had cars.

55:13.511 --> 55:18.547
Look, I don't like to say it,
but why'd anybody do that

55:18.549 --> 55:23.052
to his own mama
in her house and all?

55:24.321 --> 55:25.821
Hey!

55:55.485 --> 55:59.121
<i>Drought conditions
continue all over the south and southwest.</i>

55:59.123 --> 56:02.725
<i>Cleanup is well underway
in Saint John the baptist</i>

56:02.727 --> 56:04.760
<i>and Jefferson parishes
this evening</i>

56:04.762 --> 56:08.764
<i>as localized flood waters
continue to recede...</i>

56:08.766 --> 56:10.399
Hey, hey, baby.

56:12.369 --> 56:15.371
Crank that ac up higher,
would you, byrd?

56:15.373 --> 56:17.139
Hang on a sec.

56:19.876 --> 56:21.944
Ohh...

56:21.946 --> 56:23.011
Okay.

56:23.013 --> 56:26.448
Getting crazier by the minute.

56:26.450 --> 56:30.853
What else is new?
No, worse.

56:30.855 --> 56:32.888
I can't.

56:32.890 --> 56:34.089
It's one more day...

56:34.091 --> 56:37.459
I can hear you, goddamn it!
- Hang on.

57:35.218 --> 57:37.085
Why would you elect
to sit out here

57:37.087 --> 57:39.755
instead of staying inside
where it's cool?

57:39.757 --> 57:43.091
Wanted to give you
some privacy.

57:43.093 --> 57:45.894
How's geri?
- Ticked off at you.

57:45.896 --> 57:48.664
I'll take you both out
to the chatterbox for dinner

57:48.666 --> 57:51.467
when we get back,
my treat.

57:52.602 --> 57:55.137
You know, today when I was
talking to buford,

57:55.139 --> 57:58.740
I was trying to get him to
remember something about Walker,

57:58.742 --> 58:03.479
and it put me back
into that room that night.

58:03.481 --> 58:08.517
I started...
Remembering his toes.

58:08.519 --> 58:09.618
They were all curled up,

58:09.620 --> 58:11.720
and I was standing
at the foot of his bed

58:11.722 --> 58:14.223
trying to straighten them out,
and they...

58:14.225 --> 58:17.125
they would not straighten.

58:17.127 --> 58:22.231
I guess I stood there
for a long time, but...

58:22.233 --> 58:24.967
Maybe it was only
a couple of minutes,

58:24.969 --> 58:28.103
the way he was laying there
and all the blood, and...

58:28.105 --> 58:33.942
and me looking for a note,
and there wasn't a note.

58:33.944 --> 58:35.210
And...

58:35.212 --> 58:39.047
One side of his briefs
were kind of pulled down,

58:39.049 --> 58:41.984
and I could see...

58:41.986 --> 58:45.187
His birthmark,
that weird brown mark.

58:45.189 --> 58:48.123
That was shaped like a smile.
- Huh?

58:48.125 --> 58:50.859
Nothing.
- No.

58:50.861 --> 58:54.129
You said his birthmark
was shaped like a smile.

58:54.131 --> 58:56.265
That was...

58:58.968 --> 59:01.270
...in a real private area
of his body.

59:01.272 --> 59:02.538
How would you know that?

59:02.540 --> 59:07.075
Well, I saw him changing when
we went swimming at the shore.

59:07.077 --> 59:08.844
Uh-huh.

59:10.113 --> 59:11.780
And that's it?

59:11.782 --> 59:13.615
What else could it be?

59:13.617 --> 59:16.585
Well, I don't know,
birdie byrd.

59:16.587 --> 59:18.253
You tell me.

59:20.290 --> 59:22.324
Nothing to tell.

59:42.245 --> 59:45.681
Okay, okay, okay.
There was this period of time...

59:45.683 --> 59:48.584
oh, my god.
Oh, my god.

59:48.586 --> 59:49.985
It wasn't like he was a kid.
He was 23.

59:49.987 --> 59:51.853
So that made you what,
how old?

59:51.855 --> 59:53.255
I don't know,
32, I guess.

59:53.257 --> 59:56.592
Look, I didn't know how to talk
to you about it when it happened,

59:56.594 --> 59:57.759
and then Walker passed,
and now...

59:57.761 --> 01:00:00.729
I never wanted to tell you.
I knew you'd blow your stack.

01:00:00.731 --> 01:00:03.799
So this is about
how I'd react?

01:00:03.801 --> 01:00:05.233
Jesus Christ, byrd!

01:00:05.235 --> 01:00:08.203
You've been in that truck with
me for how many hours,

01:00:08.205 --> 01:00:11.106
and didn't think to...
oh, now I get it.

01:00:11.108 --> 01:00:12.240
Now I get it.

01:00:12.242 --> 01:00:14.176
You were just coming along
for the ride

01:00:14.178 --> 01:00:15.177
because you were atoning.

01:00:15.179 --> 01:00:18.246
No, no, what the hell would
i need to atone for, Darcy?

01:00:18.248 --> 01:00:20.983
Isn't it obvious?
- No, no, it is not.

01:00:20.985 --> 01:00:22.784
Here's some news for you...
other people cared

01:00:22.786 --> 01:00:24.620
about Walker, too,
and they had their own reasons.

01:00:24.622 --> 01:00:27.089
Not everything has to do with you.
- Excuse me?

01:00:27.091 --> 01:00:29.958
You don't think I had to ask
myself some questions

01:00:29.960 --> 01:00:30.993
when Walker died?

01:00:30.995 --> 01:00:33.829
I didn't even realize
how much he was keeping from me.

01:00:33.831 --> 01:00:36.732
He talked to me about
the stars and the moon

01:00:36.734 --> 01:00:37.799
and theories of the universe.

01:00:37.801 --> 01:00:39.668
For god's sake, do you know
how many times I had to

01:00:39.670 --> 01:00:42.104
ask myself why he didn't come
over and see me that night?

01:00:42.106 --> 01:00:44.406
I was right across the street.
- No, you were not.

01:00:44.408 --> 01:00:47.009
When I called you,
you were at your sister's.

01:00:47.011 --> 01:00:49.645
That was a whole day later.

01:00:56.019 --> 01:00:58.220
So how did it...

01:00:58.222 --> 01:00:59.721
how'd it get started?

01:00:59.723 --> 01:01:02.691
I don't want to get
into that.

01:01:02.693 --> 01:01:04.292
I'm sorry.
I gotta know.

01:01:04.294 --> 01:01:08.930
Well, not that I think you have
any right to this information,

01:01:08.932 --> 01:01:10.232
but look, I was lonely.

01:01:10.234 --> 01:01:11.199
Walker was lonely, too.

01:01:11.201 --> 01:01:12.934
He was starting to get
those mood swings,

01:01:12.936 --> 01:01:15.170
and I think maybe at first,
he just needed the company.

01:01:15.172 --> 01:01:17.072
And you were all caught up
with Clay, in case you forgot,

01:01:17.074 --> 01:01:18.907
and you didn't really
want Walker around too much,

01:01:18.909 --> 01:01:22.811
also in case you forgot.
- So I wasn't supposed to have a boyfriend?

01:01:22.813 --> 01:01:24.112
And Walker wasn't
supposed to have

01:01:24.114 --> 01:01:25.347
his own life,
his own feelings?

01:01:25.349 --> 01:01:28.083
He wasn't carved out of stone
in your mirror image, you know.

01:01:28.085 --> 01:01:29.317
We were like two peas
in a pod.

01:01:29.319 --> 01:01:31.353
That's exactly
what I'm talking about, Darcy!

01:01:31.355 --> 01:01:35.724
It's like the way you see the
world's the only way to see it.

01:01:35.726 --> 01:01:36.925
It's like some cardinal truth.

01:01:36.927 --> 01:01:38.760
But that's just the story
you've been telling yourself.

01:01:38.762 --> 01:01:41.129
That doesn't mean that's
how it actually was.

01:01:41.131 --> 01:01:42.164
I was there.

01:01:42.166 --> 01:01:45.233
Sometimes Walker hated your guts
just like any kid does.

01:01:48.439 --> 01:01:50.439
Sometimes he tried
to make himself

01:01:50.441 --> 01:01:51.940
as different from you
as he could.

01:01:51.942 --> 01:01:53.341
Is it any surprise
his apartment

01:01:53.343 --> 01:01:57.412
only had brand-new stuff in it,
nothing old or remotely antique?

01:01:57.414 --> 01:02:00.315
Is it any surprise
he voted republican twice?

01:02:00.317 --> 01:02:05.454
So what you're telling me
is I was a shitty mother.

01:02:05.456 --> 01:02:07.289
No.
- Just say it then.

01:02:07.291 --> 01:02:10.192
Say I was shitty and selfish
and I let my son

01:02:10.194 --> 01:02:11.993
slip through my fingers
and that I didn't see

01:02:11.995 --> 01:02:14.029
a goddamn thing
that was going on with him

01:02:14.031 --> 01:02:15.864
when he was staring me
in the face.

01:02:15.866 --> 01:02:20.235
Darcy, he was depressed.
- I know that.

01:02:20.237 --> 01:02:21.103
I know.

01:02:21.105 --> 01:02:24.106
What kind of mother
doesn't grasp that

01:02:24.108 --> 01:02:25.440
and doesn't try to fix it?

01:02:25.442 --> 01:02:27.309
You tried.
You couldn't fix it.

01:02:27.311 --> 01:02:28.443
But what you're telling me

01:02:28.445 --> 01:02:31.046
is that I didn't see Walker
as he was.

01:02:31.048 --> 01:02:34.850
So what was I seeing then?
- You saw the parts of him

01:02:34.852 --> 01:02:36.418
you wanted to see,
just like we all do.

01:02:36.420 --> 01:02:38.954
You saw the parts of him
that reflected

01:02:38.956 --> 01:02:40.489
the right way on you.

01:02:40.491 --> 01:02:43.158
I'm just trying to figure out
some things

01:02:43.160 --> 01:02:45.093
about my boy
and how he died.

01:02:45.095 --> 01:02:45.994
Enough time passes,

01:02:45.996 --> 01:02:48.396
and nobody's even gonna
remember Walker anymore.

01:02:48.398 --> 01:02:52.334
That's not true.
- Well, it sure feels that way.

01:02:52.336 --> 01:02:55.036
And I'm sorry if i...
if I'm not evolving

01:02:55.038 --> 01:02:58.907
the way you think I should be
or Clay thinks I should be

01:02:58.909 --> 01:03:01.009
or geri thinks I should...

01:03:02.145 --> 01:03:04.780
does she know about this?

01:03:06.949 --> 01:03:10.218
Great.
Just great.

01:03:10.220 --> 01:03:13.955
And she still doesn't think
you're a dabbler?

01:03:13.957 --> 01:03:16.925
She loves me as I am.

01:03:22.431 --> 01:03:25.967
Do you know why I came
on this trip with you, Darcy?

01:03:25.969 --> 01:03:27.569
It's not because
i think you need

01:03:27.571 --> 01:03:30.539
some showdown
with mark Wright.

01:03:31.474 --> 01:03:33.475
No, I came with you
because I want to see you

01:03:33.477 --> 01:03:36.878
find a way to come back
and live in this world again

01:03:36.880 --> 01:03:39.381
before you let this kill you.

01:03:42.318 --> 01:03:45.954
You're one of the most amazing
people I know.

01:03:45.956 --> 01:03:50.892
You're so tough and so funny
and so damn smart.

01:03:50.894 --> 01:03:52.360
You show me lots of ways
to think about

01:03:52.362 --> 01:03:55.463
how to be a woman in this world,
and most of the time,

01:03:55.465 --> 01:03:57.132
there's nobody
I'd rather talk to,

01:03:57.134 --> 01:03:59.201
and that's including geri,
but you can't ask everybody

01:03:59.203 --> 01:04:02.604
to keep standing by and watch
you put yourself through this.

01:04:02.606 --> 01:04:04.973
Everybody who loves you
deserves better.

01:04:04.975 --> 01:04:06.041
I know I do.

01:04:06.043 --> 01:04:08.977
I had a really good time
with Walker.

01:04:08.979 --> 01:04:12.113
I cared for him a whole lot.

01:04:13.349 --> 01:04:15.217
He was special.

01:04:15.219 --> 01:04:16.184
He was fragile.

01:04:16.186 --> 01:04:19.855
He was here,
and then he was gone.

01:04:21.424 --> 01:04:24.426
All I can say is that
the small piece of life

01:04:24.428 --> 01:04:26.361
that was about him and me
really got lived.

01:04:26.363 --> 01:04:32.434
And that's a lot.
Sometimes that's all we got.

01:05:12.541 --> 01:05:15.010
good luck, darce.

01:05:53.115 --> 01:05:56.217
How could it have
gone out already?

01:05:56.219 --> 01:05:59.487
It was only a couple
of hours ago!

01:05:59.489 --> 01:06:02.157
It was right
under my pillow!

01:06:03.559 --> 01:06:06.261
Those papers!

01:06:06.263 --> 01:06:08.430
I need those papers!

01:06:11.702 --> 01:06:14.102
Now what, Darcy?

01:06:14.104 --> 01:06:15.537
What now?!

01:08:09.452 --> 01:08:13.488
I'm going
to mark's office.

01:08:28.237 --> 01:08:30.104
Excuse me, ma'am,
may I help you?

01:08:30.107 --> 01:08:34.843
I'm here to see mark Wright.
Addie bundren?

01:08:39.715 --> 01:08:43.184
Um, what is this here
at the bottom?

01:08:43.185 --> 01:08:45.353
Oh, that's just a standard
clause acknowledging

01:08:45.354 --> 01:08:47.188
that the dawg house
and its franchises

01:08:47.189 --> 01:08:50.258
are the exclusive property
of Mr. Wright.

01:08:50.260 --> 01:08:52.460
Oh, okay.

01:09:03.506 --> 01:09:06.207
Here we go.

01:09:06.774 --> 01:09:08.910
Exactly, look,
you gotta hold on right there.

01:09:08.912 --> 01:09:11.279
Let them know
you mean business.

01:09:11.281 --> 01:09:15.550
Uh-huh.
Yeah, you got it.

01:09:15.551 --> 01:09:16.718
I gotta fly.

01:09:16.720 --> 01:09:19.254
I'll catch you
on the flipside, buddy.

01:09:19.822 --> 01:09:24.759
I'm so sorry, Ms. bundren.
Come on, please take a seat.

01:09:24.761 --> 01:09:26.361
It's been a busy day
for us here,

01:09:26.363 --> 01:09:29.596
but I did want to make time
to see you.

01:09:29.599 --> 01:09:31.733
I've had my eye on Mississippi
for a while now.

01:09:31.734 --> 01:09:35.803
So, uh, you already running
restaurants down there, or?

01:09:35.805 --> 01:09:41.509
I'm sorry, you want to...
you want to sit down?

01:09:41.911 --> 01:09:45.180
All right,
so why do you want to put

01:09:45.182 --> 01:09:48.349
Mississippi
in the dawg house?

01:09:48.350 --> 01:09:51.553
Well...

01:09:51.555 --> 01:09:53.787
It seems like, um,

01:09:53.790 --> 01:09:56.858
everybody likes
a family restaurant, right?

01:09:56.860 --> 01:09:58.826
It's a business
you can't go wrong with.

01:09:58.828 --> 01:10:02.764
I mean, no matter what
the economy is like,

01:10:02.766 --> 01:10:05.767
parents always want to take
their kids out to eat.

01:10:05.769 --> 01:10:07.569
That's the truth.
That's the truth.

01:10:07.571 --> 01:10:08.937
You could ask my wife
all about that.

01:10:08.939 --> 01:10:12.574
She says a wife just needs
to take a break every so often

01:10:12.576 --> 01:10:14.309
from putting dinner
on the table.

01:10:14.311 --> 01:10:16.244
Yeah.
- All right, so tell me,

01:10:16.246 --> 01:10:17.445
what are you picturing,
Ms. bundren?

01:10:17.447 --> 01:10:19.314
You wanna start out with the one
dawg house and build them up?

01:10:19.316 --> 01:10:22.517
Well, that's the way
to a grow business, right?

01:10:22.519 --> 01:10:25.887
I heard you got your start by
selling t-shirts at rock shows.

01:10:25.889 --> 01:10:28.856
Yeah, somebody's
been doing their homework.

01:10:28.858 --> 01:10:33.294
Well, you know,
it's all there on the website.

01:10:33.296 --> 01:10:37.699
I'm just curious,
where'd you get that idea from?

01:10:37.701 --> 01:10:38.566
Uh...

01:10:38.568 --> 01:10:41.469
Just seemed like a natural way
to generate some capital,

01:10:41.471 --> 01:10:42.537
get things moving.

01:10:42.539 --> 01:10:45.873
What band did you
make shirts for?

01:10:47.777 --> 01:10:51.546
Who... who's
interviewing who here, huh?

01:10:53.617 --> 01:10:55.283
Oh, sorry.
Um...

01:10:55.285 --> 01:10:57.318
So in terms of setting up
a franchise,

01:10:57.320 --> 01:11:00.321
would you say that parents
are looking for a place

01:11:00.323 --> 01:11:01.756
that's bright and clean
for the kids,

01:11:01.758 --> 01:11:04.259
a place where their needs
are taken into account?

01:11:04.261 --> 01:11:06.261
And then you need
to make sure the chain

01:11:06.263 --> 01:11:09.264
gives back into the community
to build a brand.

01:11:09.266 --> 01:11:11.833
I guess you can find out
just about anything

01:11:11.835 --> 01:11:13.034
on the Internet these days.

01:11:13.036 --> 01:11:15.270
That sounds a lot
like my business plan.

01:11:15.272 --> 01:11:17.939
Except it's not
your business plan.

01:11:17.941 --> 01:11:19.674
Pardon me?

01:11:19.676 --> 01:11:22.977
It's from a business plan,
all right.

01:11:22.979 --> 01:11:25.313
But it's not yours.

01:11:29.718 --> 01:11:34.055
So I'm not sure what
you're getting at, Ms...

01:11:34.057 --> 01:11:38.860
Baylor, actually.
Darcy baylor.

01:11:38.862 --> 01:11:41.296
I guess I wasn't important
enough for you to remember,

01:11:41.298 --> 01:11:42.697
but you met me
a bunch of times

01:11:42.699 --> 01:11:45.433
back when you and Walker
were friends.

01:11:45.435 --> 01:11:49.370
I'm sorry, I did know
a Walker baylor

01:11:49.372 --> 01:11:50.071
back in school but...

01:11:50.073 --> 01:11:53.007
looks like you're still
doing coke.

01:11:53.009 --> 01:11:55.943
A whole lot of coke.

01:11:55.945 --> 01:11:57.679
Am I right?

01:11:57.681 --> 01:11:59.080
I'm calling the cops.

01:11:59.082 --> 01:12:00.915
You really want
to mix them up in this?

01:12:00.917 --> 01:12:02.617
I'm sorry, ma'am,
not to be rude,

01:12:02.619 --> 01:12:05.053
but take a look at yourself,
and take a look at me.

01:12:05.055 --> 01:12:07.388
Who do you think they're
gonna believe?

01:12:07.390 --> 01:12:07.989
What the hell?

01:12:07.991 --> 01:12:12.393
I am Darcy baylor,
and I am Walker baylor's mother,

01:12:12.395 --> 01:12:15.830
and you are not to diminish
or belittle us,

01:12:15.832 --> 01:12:17.632
do you understand me?

01:12:22.037 --> 01:12:24.505
How much do you want?

01:12:24.507 --> 01:12:25.540
Come again?

01:12:25.542 --> 01:12:26.808
How much money do you want?

01:12:26.810 --> 01:12:28.743
You think I'm here
for your money?

01:12:28.745 --> 01:12:32.347
Don't insult me.

01:12:32.349 --> 01:12:35.717
I want you to tell me
what happened

01:12:35.719 --> 01:12:37.719
the day Walker died.

01:12:38.654 --> 01:12:40.688
What the hell happened?

01:12:41.090 --> 01:12:44.859
Every damn detail.
I need you to tell me why.

01:12:44.861 --> 01:12:46.060
Why what?

01:12:46.062 --> 01:12:48.429
Why he killed himself.

01:12:48.431 --> 01:12:51.132
Why he...
i don't know why.

01:12:51.134 --> 01:12:52.800
But you know
what his last hours

01:12:52.802 --> 01:12:55.103
on this planet were like,
and that's what you need

01:12:55.105 --> 01:12:57.071
to tell me about right now.

01:12:57.073 --> 01:13:00.842
I mean it. Now.

01:13:07.015 --> 01:13:10.451
This is crazy.
This is crazy.

01:13:14.123 --> 01:13:16.057
I guess.

01:13:16.059 --> 01:13:18.526
Okay.

01:13:18.528 --> 01:13:23.564
Walker was...
he was so goddamn bummed out.

01:13:23.566 --> 01:13:25.099
What was he bummed out about?

01:13:25.101 --> 01:13:28.569
Stuff, just...

01:13:28.571 --> 01:13:29.537
I had a daddy with means.

01:13:29.539 --> 01:13:31.606
I couldn't possibly know
what he was talking about.

01:13:31.608 --> 01:13:33.408
I was probably
gonna graduate on time.

01:13:33.410 --> 01:13:34.809
He probably wasn't
gonna make it.

01:13:34.811 --> 01:13:37.578
And then, what kind of job
was he gonna be able to get?

01:13:37.580 --> 01:13:41.048
Could he ever get married,
have a family of his own?

01:13:41.050 --> 01:13:41.783
Stuff like that.

01:13:41.785 --> 01:13:45.119
I was like, "little man,
if life is that tough,

01:13:45.121 --> 01:13:47.789
do us all a favor,
all right, and put yourself

01:13:47.791 --> 01:13:51.459
out of your misery because
you're bringing us down."

01:13:51.461 --> 01:13:54.762
Stuff like that.
I was just messing with him.

01:13:55.464 --> 01:13:57.165
Shit!

01:14:01.870 --> 01:14:03.738
And then, uh...

01:14:04.840 --> 01:14:09.477
And then we all went upstairs,
and I guess I fell asleep,

01:14:09.479 --> 01:14:10.978
because when I woke up,
it was real late.

01:14:10.980 --> 01:14:14.916
It was just me and Walker
in the room at that point.

01:14:14.918 --> 01:14:20.655
And he was sitting over by
the window in a rocking chair.

01:14:21.623 --> 01:14:24.859
Real quiet
just rocking back and forth,

01:14:24.861 --> 01:14:26.894
looking out the window.

01:14:26.896 --> 01:14:30.231
And he asked me if I'd give
him a ride back into town.

01:14:30.233 --> 01:14:32.033
I was still pretty messed up
by then.

01:14:32.035 --> 01:14:34.569
But I said all right.

01:14:36.572 --> 01:14:38.506
So I did.

01:14:38.874 --> 01:14:42.009
I'm curious.

01:14:42.011 --> 01:14:44.712
Since you were the last one
to see him alive,

01:14:44.714 --> 01:14:47.515
what did he say to you
when you...

01:14:47.517 --> 01:14:50.685
when you dropped him off
at my doorstep?

01:14:52.788 --> 01:14:54.589
It was a long time ago.

01:14:54.591 --> 01:14:56.123
Honestly, I don't recall.

01:14:56.125 --> 01:15:00.895
It was just a night
like any other night for me.

01:15:00.897 --> 01:15:03.064
Did you ask him...

01:15:05.901 --> 01:15:08.102
What was on his mind?

01:15:08.104 --> 01:15:12.273
Because I'm guessing it was
pretty obvious he was upset.

01:15:12.275 --> 01:15:17.645
It was obvious
he needed somebody to talk to.

01:15:17.647 --> 01:15:18.880
I was at work that night.

01:15:18.882 --> 01:15:20.948
I didn't get home
till it was nearly dawn.

01:15:20.950 --> 01:15:26.621
So did he say anything
about me by any chance?

01:15:26.623 --> 01:15:28.222
I don't think so.

01:15:28.224 --> 01:15:30.124
I mean, come on,
guys that age,

01:15:30.126 --> 01:15:34.195
we don't talk about our moms,
you know what I mean?

01:15:44.072 --> 01:15:46.541
Why'd you give him
the bullets?

01:15:46.543 --> 01:15:47.742
What?
- The bullets.

01:15:47.744 --> 01:15:50.578
All these years, I've been
trying to figure it out,

01:15:50.580 --> 01:15:52.280
and there was that
one missing piece,

01:15:52.282 --> 01:15:54.916
but now it all makes sense.

01:15:55.984 --> 01:15:58.319
Walker says he's given up
on his dreams,

01:15:58.321 --> 01:16:03.057
y'all get all lit up,
you go in your room,

01:16:03.059 --> 01:16:05.560
you give him the bullets.

01:16:05.562 --> 01:16:07.061
No, oh, no, no, ma'am.

01:16:07.063 --> 01:16:10.231
Then you drove Walker
back to my house,

01:16:10.233 --> 01:16:13.167
let him go in,
shoot himself.

01:16:13.169 --> 01:16:15.336
And you got to take away
his business plan.

01:16:15.338 --> 01:16:17.171
Perfect, right?
- No, ma'am.

01:16:17.173 --> 01:16:19.774
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
slow it down now.

01:16:19.776 --> 01:16:21.042
You stole everything
from my child.

01:16:21.044 --> 01:16:25.146
I swear, ma'am, I swear,
i n... no, don't shoot me!

01:16:25.148 --> 01:16:27.615
I swear on my daughter
Bella's life,

01:16:27.617 --> 01:16:29.083
I never gave Walker
any bullets!

01:16:29.085 --> 01:16:31.218
Dennis.
Remember Dennis?

01:16:31.220 --> 01:16:32.687
Oh, my god,
please don't shoot me!

01:16:32.689 --> 01:16:33.888
He told me he saw
a box of bullets

01:16:33.890 --> 01:16:36.090
in Walker's hand when
he came out of your room.

01:16:36.092 --> 01:16:38.326
I had guns and ammo
lying all over the place!

01:16:38.328 --> 01:16:40.261
I didn't... I didn't even keep
my bullets <i> in</i> a box!

01:16:40.263 --> 01:16:42.830
What about buford?
Buford said you saw a door open up,

01:16:42.832 --> 01:16:46.300
and you walked right through it.
You took Walker's plan...

01:16:46.302 --> 01:16:48.302
my daddy told me
i had to come out of school

01:16:48.304 --> 01:16:49.770
with something
to show for it!

01:16:49.772 --> 01:16:52.306
After Walker passed, I guess
i figured I'd get something.

01:16:52.308 --> 01:16:55.610
I knew daddy could get behind
a restaurant chain.

01:16:55.612 --> 01:16:57.945
I could make it fly, so...

01:16:57.947 --> 01:16:59.246
So...

01:17:01.683 --> 01:17:04.285
You took Walker's plan...

01:17:04.287 --> 01:17:08.356
To stay out of trouble
with your daddy.

01:17:11.827 --> 01:17:17.832
Then why'd you go and try
and turn yourself into Walker?

01:17:19.234 --> 01:17:24.171
Getting a dog like his,

01:17:24.173 --> 01:17:29.210
taking his memories,
stealing his ideas, why?

01:17:29.344 --> 01:17:32.346
Didn't you have any memories
of your own?!

01:17:32.348 --> 01:17:36.651
I didn't have any stories
that good.

01:17:36.653 --> 01:17:39.120
I didn't have what he had
back at that time.

01:17:39.122 --> 01:17:43.257
I didn't have anything
that seemed like it would work.

01:17:44.326 --> 01:17:47.161
I remember thinking
i wish my mom and me

01:17:47.163 --> 01:17:49.230
could be like you two were.

01:17:49.232 --> 01:17:53.734
It's funny 'cause
he thought I had everything.

01:17:53.736 --> 01:17:55.403
At the end of the day...

01:17:55.405 --> 01:17:57.304
no, no, wait!
Please, please, please.

01:17:57.306 --> 01:18:01.375
What did it feel like
for him...

01:18:01.377 --> 01:18:02.910
In that moment?

01:18:02.912 --> 01:18:07.081
Stop!
- Cold.

01:18:07.083 --> 01:18:08.449
Scary.

01:18:08.451 --> 01:18:09.884
And then...

01:18:09.886 --> 01:18:11.452
... Black.

01:18:11.454 --> 01:18:13.354
No.

01:22:31.113 --> 01:22:32.313
You know, it's funny,

01:22:32.315 --> 01:22:33.681
sometimes I'll be going
down the sidewalk,

01:22:33.683 --> 01:22:38.218
not thinking about
anything in particular, and...

01:22:44.492 --> 01:22:48.963
I'll feel your hand
sliding into mine.

01:22:52.167 --> 01:22:55.602
Even though
i know it's not there.

01:22:57.505 --> 01:23:01.608
Even though I know
it's never going to be there.

01:23:10.552 --> 01:23:14.588
I can't tell you
what I would give...

01:23:14.590 --> 01:23:17.591
To hold your hand again.

01:23:23.298 --> 01:23:25.599
My baby boy.

01:23:57.098 --> 01:23:59.366
Glad to see
you made it home okay.

01:23:59.368 --> 01:24:01.568
Judging from your shirt,
looks like you still got a job.

01:24:01.570 --> 01:24:06.740
I do, and you can tell geri
she can start working her magic.

01:24:06.742 --> 01:24:09.176
You got it in?
Tell her yourself.

